    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, the tension part. But what happens if there's something going on inside the concrete that we can't see? Like, if there are tiny cracks or imperfections forming in the middle of the slab where the rebar is, does that affect the bond between the two materials? How does the steel actually stop those internal issues from spreading?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
